properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued February 8 at 11:39AM AKST until February 10 at 6:00AM AKST by NWS Fairbanks, AK
properties.description:
* WHAT...Snow and blowing snow expected. Plan on areas of poor
visibility and difficult travel conditions. Total snow
accumulations of up to three inches are expected.

* WHERE...Northeastern Brooks Range.

* WHEN...Midnight to 6 AM Monday.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Winds gusting as high as 30 mph will cause
areas of blowing and drifting snow. Locally Wind Chill to 50
below can cause frostbite in  as little as 10 minutes to
exposed skin.
properties.instruction:
A Winter Weather Advisory for snow and blowing snow means periods
of snow and blowing snow will cause travel difficulties. The
latest road conditions can be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM MIDNIGHT TONIGHT TO 6 AM AKST MONDAY
